Passport required.
- Passports and other documents accepted for entry must be
  valid for the period of intended stay. 
 - British Passports endorsed British Citizen or British
   Overseas Territories Citizen must be valid on arrival.   
- British passports endorsed  British Citizen  that have been
  extended 12 months by an extension stamp contained within
  the passport are accepted.
Passport Exemptions:
- Holders of proof of citizenship issued to residents of the
  Cayman Isl.
- Holders of emergency or temporary passports.

Visa required, except for Holders of British Passports
endorsed  British Overseas Territories Citizen  issued by the
Cayman Isl.. 
Visa required, except for Holders of proof of citizenship
issued to residents of Cayman Isl..
Visa required, except for Holders of British passports
endorsed  British Citizen  also holding a Caymanian Status
Certificate or expired  British Overseas Territories Citizen 
passport issued by the Cayman Isl.
Visa required, except for Holders of British passports
endorsed  British Citizen  (SEE NOTE 55485) (SEE NOTE 55486).
    NOTE 55485: for a max. stay of 60 days when traveling as
   tourist.
    NOTE 55486: for a max. stay of 10 days when traveling for
   business purposes.
Visa required, except for Holders of British passports
endorsed  British Overseas Territories Citizen  (SEE NOTE
55485) (SEE NOTE 55486), issued by  .
    NOTE 55485: for a max. stay of 60 days when traveling as
   tourist.
    NOTE 55486: for a max. stay of 10 days when traveling for
   business purposes.
Visa required, except for A max. stay of 30 days for holders
of British passports endorsed  British National (Overseas) ,
 British Overseas Citizen ,  British Subject  or  British
Protected Person" who have been granted "Indefinite Leave to
Remain" in the United Kingdom and arriving directly from the
United Kingdom. 
Additional Information:
- Visitors are required to hold proof of sufficient funds to
  cover their stay and documents required for their next
  destination.
- The period of stay granted for all visitors will be
  determined by the Immigration Officer on arrival.
- Extension of tourist stay possible up to a total stay of 180
  days.
Warning:
- Nationals of United Kingdom who have visited Guinea, Liberia
  or Sierra Leone within the last 21 days will be refused
  entry. 
- Visitors not holding return/onward tickets  co
  uld be refused entry.
